<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="K" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Kindred" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Kindred</orth> (O. Edd. sometimes <emph>kinred</emph>), 1) relations, race: <bibl n="shak. lc 270" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 270</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.32" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.186" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 186</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.138" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.72" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.72" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 72</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.67" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.135" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 135</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.150" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.212" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 212</bibl> (Qq <emph>kin</emph>). <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.223" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 223</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.254" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 254</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.344" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 344</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.168" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 168</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.429" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 429</bibl>. The verb following in the sing.: <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 1, 199</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 30.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 50</bibl>. In the plural: <bibl n="shak. h8 3.1.150" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 1, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 1, 112</bibl>. Adjectively: <cit><quote>k. blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.182" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 182</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>k. tears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 63</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) relationship: <cit><quote>disclaiming here the k. of the king,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 70</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>whom conscience and my k. bids to right,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.115" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 115</bibl></cit>. Metaphorically: <cit><quote>stirrups of no k.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 50</bibl></cit>. Adjectively: <cit><quote>any k. action,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 14</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>